Ten persons have lost their lives in an auto crash that occurred at Hakayafi village between Rimin Zayan and Nabordo on the Bauchi-Jos highway on Thursday afternoon. Though details of the fatal accident is still sketchy, DAILY POST gathered it occurred about 1:30pm and involved a Hummer bus and a Sienna car coming in the opposite directions. It was learnt that the vehicles had a head-on collision, leading to one of them bursting in flames. Some of the victims of the crash were said to have been caught in the flames and were burnt to death. The Bauchi State Sector of the Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) is yet to comment on the accident as of the time of filing this report. Details later.